race.comment: RIVER ANGEL (12) bounced back to form last start when leading the field in a CL3 at Bunbury most recently. Pike replaces the apprentice hoop today in a big push for her chances. She remains down in the weights and the rise in trip should suit. Can go one better this time around. BONNY ROCK (6) won narrowly two back before turning in another solid figure when beaten in a photo at Geraldton last time out. This shapes similarly today for Faithfull and coming back in trip slightly looks a good move. Can return to winning ways. IMAPAGETHREE GIRL (7) is racing in good order recently and is on the quick turnaround today. Recent ratings stack right up and while she hasn't won for a while, it wouldn't surprise to see the drought end here. WHERE'S MY LUNCH (3) can feature in the finish first-up despite coming in without a trial. SECRET STONES (8) is a winner over this trip previously and won't be far away.
